{
  "stem": "12491.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And we ate it all-- carrots, raw tomatoes, raw beets-- as bad as they were-- and stuff like that.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And we eventually wound up in eastern Poland, and crossed the river Bug, B-U-G, and wound up in the part of Poland which was, at that point, occupied by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So actually, we were in a Russian-occupied part of Poland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "From there, we tried to go to a town on the Romanian-- Romanian and-- and Hungarian border, Tarnopol, T-A-R-N-O-P-O-L.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Because we were told that the border is open, and they're allowing people to go through, and wind up in Italy, and hopefully, eventually, in Palestine.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But when we arrived there, because there was no good transportation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Most of the bridge was walking.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We had realized that the border was not open.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And we had to just turn back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "To turn back, we went to a farm in eastern Poland, under the Russian rule at that time, which was in a-- a-- in a town, known Rava Ruska, capital R-A-V-A, R-- capital R-U-S-K-A.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And this farm-- donated at one time by wealthy Jews in Crakow-- was training Halutzim in agriculture so they would go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Since my older brother was one of the [NON-ENGLISH], or managers in the-- in Akiba, and the farm was controlled by Akiba, we were allowed to-- when we arrived there, we were allowed to move in there and stay with them.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But with the next few days, so many people arrived and stayed with us, that it was more than 100 of us there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Well, the farm was only intended for about 25 or 30 people at a time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Therefore, the farm could not support all that group of people.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
